benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/block - Block a bundle

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC26, @TC27, @TC29 cover successful creation with valid data and various parameter combinations.
Invalid Payload: @TC08 covers malformed request body; @TC11 covers invalid requestedDate format.
Missing Headers: @TC09 covers missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header.
Missing Body: @TC10 covers absence of request body.
Invalid bundleId: @TC06 covers invalid format; @TC07 covers non-existent bundleId.
Not Found: @TC05 and @TC07 cover scenarios where bundle does not exist.
Extra Parameters: @TC12 covers unexpected query or header parameters.
Maximum/Minimum Values: @TC13 and @TC14 test boundary values.
Partial Input: @TC15 tests partial data submission.
Large Payload: @TC16 stress test with large data.
Injection/XSS: @TC19 and @TC20 test for injection and XSS payloads.
Concurrency & Retry: @TC22 and @TC21 cover concurrent requests and network retries.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC23 and @TC24 ensure backward compatibility and fixed issues.
Performance: @TC25, @TC26, @TC27 test response times and resource utilization.
Dependency Errors: @TC28 simulates dependent service failures.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets requiring pagination.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized or invalid tokens beyond @TC09.
Rate Limiting: No scenarios testing system behavior under high request rates.
Caching Behavior: No tests verifying cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Service Unavailability: Limited coverage of server downtime or network failures beyond retries.
Soft Deletes or Data Recovery: No tests for soft delete behaviors or data recovery scenarios.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling to verify correct response with large datasets.
Include explicit authorization tests with invalid or missing tokens to ensure security.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system robustness under load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
Test server downtime, network failures, and recovery to improve resilience coverage.
Include tests for soft delete and data recovery processes if applicable.
